The paper focuses on improving the performance of image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves building a Confusion Visual Tree (CVT) to identify confused categories, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning (cs.NE) and evaluation on benchmark datasets (cs.IR).
